{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H7hGxxiqpGsWpyp1pa7MjL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is invoking `/spec-realign` with the argument \"認証セッションとCSRFの仕様に従って、ログイン後セッションと状態変更リクエストの扱いを回答して\". \n\nLet me follow the mandatory steps:\n\n1. Define the task from the argument and conversation context\n2. Generate search keys\n3. Perform Agentic Search (4 paths: inject-search + inject-section, inject-chapters, inject-purpose, inject-conflicts)\n4. Build constraints JSON\n5. Self-check constraints\n6. Build answer candidate\n7. Format with 4 sections\n\n\n8. Run `spec-anchor realign --answer-json '<json>'`\n9. Present formatted result\n\nThe task centers on authentication session and CSRF specifications, focusing on how to handle post-login sessions and state-changing requests. I need to check if the config file exists in the current working directory, then proceed with the agentic search using key terms like session management, CSRF protection, login session handling, and state change request handling.\n\nNow I'm going to hand this off to an agent to execute the full spec-realign workflow.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11424,"cache_read_input_tokens":13470,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11424},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9429e1e-7c93-460a-a235-2565e60843da","uuid":"ab4b13ef-1f83-48d3-b6d4-86ae04fcd7ee","request_id":"req_011CbHtnyNYK2aV8f1zG9RWR"}
